{{external|rs=bird's nest}}
'''Bird nests''' are items found through activities such as [[Woodcutting]], [[bird house trapping]], and killing the [[Giant mole]]. There are several varieties of nests, which either contain [[seeds]], [[ring]]s, or [[bird's egg]]s.

Most activities reward a random selection of seed, ring, and egg nests. Additionally, some activities reward [[clue nest]]s, which contain a [[clue scroll]]. Opening all types of clue nests except [[Clue nest (beginner)|beginner]] will provide an empty nest. 

==Obtaining==
*Randomly dropped while [[Woodcutting]].
**The chance of getting a bird nest from a tree is 1/256 each time you would normally get a log, regardless of the type of tree. 
**Players who equip a [[Woodcutting cape]] will have an additional 10% chance of receiving bird nests from chopping trees.
*Reward from [[Managing Miscellania]] when subjects are tasked with collecting maple, teak or mahogany logs.
*Reward from offering [[bird's egg]]s to the [[shrine]] in the [[Woodcutting Guild]].
*Received from [[Wyson the gardener]] in [[Falador Park]] in exchange for [[mole claw]] and [[mole skin]].
*Received when emptying [[Hunter#Bird house trapping|bird house traps]] on [[Fossil Island]].
*Received when chopping [[ent]] trunks.
*Received as a possible tip during [[Gnome Restaurant]] minigame.

==Types of nests==
===Seed nest===
{{Main|Bird nest (seeds)}}
Seed nests contain a random [[tree seed|tree]] or [[fruit tree seed]]. These nests can be obtained through Woodcutting, bird house trapping, chopping [[ent]] trunks, [[Managing Miscellania]], or during [[Gnome Restaurant]]. They can also be obtained by using a [[bird's egg]] on the [[shrine]] in the [[Woodcutting Guild]].

Wearing a [[strung rabbit foot]] decreases the chance of seed nests while woodcutting, by replacing some seed nests drops with ring and egg nests. However, wearing a strung rabbit foot while [[bird house trapping]] does not affect the chance of getting seed nests.

===Ring nest===
{{Main|Bird nest (ring)}}
Ring nests contain a random type of either [[gold ring|gold]], [[sapphire ring|sapphire]], [[emerald ring|emerald]], [[ruby ring|ruby]], or [[diamond ring]].

Ring nests are found from woodcutting, Managing Miscellania, bird house trapping, chopping ent trunks, and trading mole parts with [[Wyson]].

Wearing a strung rabbit foot while woodcutting or bird house trapping makes ring nests slightly more likely by replacing some drops of seed or empty nests.

===Egg nest===
{{Main|Bird nest (egg)}}
Egg nests contain one of the three types of [[bird's egg]]s. The colour of the egg is visible in the nest, so it is possible to tell which egg will be received before searching the nest. The eggs can be offered to the [[shrine]] in the [[Woodcutting Guild]] to receive 100 [[Prayer]] experience as well as a seed nest or piece of the [[evil chicken outfit]].

Egg nests are received from woodcutting, bird house trapping, chopping [[ent]] trunks, and [[Managing Miscellania]].

Wearing a strung rabbit foot increases the chance of getting egg nests while woodcutting or bird house trapping, by replacing some drops of seed or empty nests.

===Wyson nest===
{{Main|Bird nest (Wyson)}}
A variant type of seed nest is received from [[Wyson the gardener]] in [[Falador Park]]. These nests commonly contain low level [[allotment seeds]], but can also reward high level [[herb seed|herb]], [[tree seed|tree]], and [[fruit tree seeds]]. Wyson provides 1 nest in exchange for each [[mole claw]] and [[mole skin]] given to him. The mole parts can be noted, and will be exchanged for [[nest box]]es if there is not enough room in the inventory. These boxes can be extracted at a bank to obtain the nests.

===Clue nest===
{{Main|Clue nest}}
Clue nests are nests that can be found while training [[Woodcutting]] or emptying [[bird house trapping|bird houses]] on [[Fossil Island]]. Searching them will give players a [[clue scroll]] of the indicated difficulty, leaving an empty bird nest (excluding beginner clue nests). Like clue scrolls, players can only have one of each type of clue nest in their possession.

===Empty nest===
{{Main|Bird nest (empty)}}
Most nests produce an empty nest after searching their contents. Empty nests can be crushed with a [[pestle and mortar]] to get a [[crushed nest]], which is used in [[Herblore]] to create [[Saradomin brews]]. Bird nests are only tradeable when empty or crushed.

Some activities can also provide empty nests, such as bird house trapping and trading mole parts with Wyson.

==Discontinued nests==
===Wyson nests (2006-2016)===
{{Main|Bird nest (Wyson, 2006-2016)}}
Seed nests from [[Wyson]] originally rewarded relatively low level seeds, and were considered to not be valuable enough compared to the difficulty of the content. To improve the nests, Wyson nests were [[Update:Dragon Claws & 3rd Birthday|updated]] on [[18 February]] [[2016]] to reward more valuable seeds. Wyson nests obtained prior to this update could still exist in player banks and inventories and can be searched to provide seeds from the original reward table.

===Pre-Farming Guild===
{{Main|Bird nest (seeds, 2005-2019)}}
{{Main|Bird nest (Wyson, 2016-2019)}}
Seed nests and Wyson nests were updated on [[10 January]] [[2019]] with the [[Update:The Kebos Lowlands|release]] of the [[Farming Guild]]. All nests previously obtained would remain in banks and inventories, and new nests would be added that contained [[dragonfruit tree seed|dragonfruit]], [[celastrus seed|celastrus]], and [[redwood tree seed]]s. [[Snape grass seed]]s were also added to Wyson nests. This change was made to prevent players from obtaining large quantities of the new seeds immediately upon release of the content.

